      "directivePrompt": "---\n\n[SYSTEM DIRECTIVE: OH-MY-OPENCODE - PROMETHEUS READ-ONLY]\n\nYou are being invoked by Prometheus (Plan Builder), a planning agent restricted to .sisyphus/*.md plan files only.\n\n**CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS:**\n- DO NOT modify any files (no Write, Edit, or any file mutations)\n- DO NOT execute commands that change system state\n- DO NOT create, delete, or rename files\n- ONLY provide analysis, recommendations, and information\n\n**YOUR ROLE**: Provide consultation, research, and analysis to assist with planning.\nReturn your findings and recommendations. The actual implementation will be handled separately after planning is complete.\n\n---\n\nReview this planning session for the repository opinion_sim_system.\n\nGoal: turn the current semantic evidence -> group evolution -> reporting chain into a stronger evidence-to-decision dashboard.\n\nUser-confirmed scope:\n- opinion_sim_system only\n- keep the 3 existing demo cases\n- produce a formal .sisyphus plan artifact\n\nResearch findings:\n- `simulation/runner.py` currently outputs `input`, `profiles`, `initial_attitudes`, `trajectories`, `semantic_summary`, `semantic_state`, `semantic_trace`, `semantic_evidence`, `coverage_validation`.\n- Each trajectory currently only has `round`, `group_attitudes`, `overall_satisfaction`, `topic_distribution`.\n- `models/semantic_fusion.py` already has `evidence_trace.experts`, `fusion.stance_components`, and aliases (`stance`, `risk`, `value_frame`).\n- `reporting/deepseek_reporter.py` is a deterministic placeholder with fallback text and optional live DeepSeek mode.\n- `demo/run_demo.py` already implements a Phase2B contract with 3 cases and report envelopes.\n- `flask_app.py` exposes `/api/briefing-run` and returns a rich JSON envelope.\n- `visualization/pm_dashboard.py`, `visualization/streamlit_app.py`, and `visualization/briefing_report.py` already consume the Phase 1 trajectory/semantic_summary shape.\n\nNeed you to identify:\n- missed questions or scope creep risks\n- missing acceptance criteria\n- any guardrails or sequencing risks\n- any places where the plan should be more specific to avoid implementation ambiguity\n<!-- OMO_INTERNAL_INITIATOR -->"
